# Problem statement
The current implementation of billing settings is inconsistent and unclear. 

For Subscription plans:
- The user classes are defined in the /backend/app/config/user_classes.yaml file 
- On each class, there is no clear indication whether a class has a pricing plan or not.
- The only way to know is to see if the class is defined in one of the platform_settings table. 
- Admin frontend /billing-settings page shows subscription pricing which will then be used to create new Stripe Price object for the plans
- During first migration or config, there is no way to configure the stripe price id for the first time.

For On-demand plans:
- No config file or admin to define the plans 
- No mechanism to setup the stripe price-id

# Proposed Requirement Solutions

During deployment or initial setup, there should be a configuration file to:
For Subscription plans:
- Configure User classes with their respective pricing plans if applicable (could be a flag that shows if the class has a pricing plan)
- Define the default Subscription plan pricing 
For On-demand plans:
- Define the default On-Demand credit package via config file, including the Package Name, Price, Credit

As admin, I should be able to:
For Subscription plans:
- See all classes that have pricing plans (based on the config file)
- Make changes of the pricing plans (this is available currently)
- Load the "default" pricing plan from the config file if needed

For On-demand plans:
- See all the defined on-demand package (based on the config file)
- Make changes to the defined on-demand package (this is available currently)
- Load the "default" pricing plan from the config file if needed


# Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] User classes config file includes pricing fields (price_cents, has_plan flag)
- [ ] Default subscription pricing is loaded from config on app initial migration and loaded to the database
- [ ] Default credit packages are created from config on first migration and loaded to the database
- [ ] Admin can view all subscription pricing plans
- [ ] Admin can edit subscription pricing plans
- [ ] Admin can view all credit packages from the database
- [ ] Admin can edit credit packages
- [ ] Admin can reset subscription pricing to config defaults
- [ ] Admin can reset credit packages to config defaults
- [ ] Stripe Products/Prices are auto-created for missing config-defined items
- [ ] No manual Stripe price ID configuration needed for initial deployment
- [ ] Existing admin-customized Stripe Price IDs in the database are preserved (startup sync only fills gaps, never overwrites)

